Function to generate the R matrix¶

In [4]:
def R_gen(iterations):
    R = np.zeros((8, x_r.shape[1])) # initialize 
    for each in [x_r,x_g,x_b]: # for each of the channel
        for i in range(iterations): # number of iterations
            rand_val = random.randint(0, each.shape[0]-8)
            b = each[rand_val:rand_val+8,0:each.shape[1]]
            R = np.hstack((R,b))
    R = R[:,768:] #removing the initial zeros used for initializing and appending purposes
    return R

Function to subtract the mean vector and calculate the co-variance vector¶

In [5]:
def covar(R):
    mu_mat = np.mean(R,axis=1).reshape((8,1))
    R = R - mu_mat
    co_var = np.cov(R)
    return co_var

Function to define a DCT matrix¶

In [6]:
def dct_matrix(N):
    const = N**(-0.5)
    dct_mat = np.zeros((8,8))
    for n in range(N):
        for k in range(N):
            cosine_val = np.cos((np.pi/(2*N))*k*(2*n+1))
            dct_mat[k,n] = cosine_val*const
            
    return dct_mat
dct_mat = dct_matrix(8)

Initialization¶

In [20]:
N = Z.shape[1]
I = np.identity(Z.shape[0]) #identity matrix
rho = 0.000001 #learning rate
W = np.random.rand(Z.shape[0],Z.shape[0]) # initialzing with random values
Y = W@Z
del_W = math.inf # initializing delta W
In [21]:
while np.sum(np.abs(del_W)) > 0.0000001:  
    f_Y = Y**3 # non-linear function 1
    g_Y = np.tanh(Y) # non-linear function 2
    del_W = (N*I - (g_Y @ f_Y.T))@W # calculating the difference
    W += rho * del_W #update the W
    Y = W @ Z
X = W@Z #recovered signal with 4 sources

Short Time Fourier Transform¶

In [30]:
N = 1024 #number of point frames

Hannwindow¶

In [31]:
hann_window = np.zeros((N,1))
for n in range(N):
    hann_window[n] = (np.sin(np.pi*n/N))**2

Function to implement DFT Matrix¶

In [32]:
def dft_mat(N,mul):
    F = np.zeros((N, N),dtype=complex)
    for f in range(N):
        for n in range(N):
            F[f][n] = np.exp(mul*2*np.pi*f*n/N * 1j)
    return F
F = dft_mat(N,-1)

Function to implement STFT¶

In [33]:
def stft(x):
    X = np.ones((N,1))
    index =0
    start, end = 0, N
    while end <= x.shape[0]:
        sub_x = x[np.int64(start):np.int64(end)].reshape((N,1))
        col = sub_x * hann_window
        X=np.concatenate((X,col),axis=1)
        start+=N/2
        end+=N/2
        index+=1
    X=np.delete(X,0,axis = 1)
    res = F @ X
    #f_res = res[0:((N//2)+1),:]
    return res,X

Inverse STFT Function¶

In [34]:
def istft(new_S):
    F_star = dft_mat(N,1)/N
    X_hat = np.dot(F_star,new_S)
    result_pad = X_hat[:,0].reshape((N,1)).T
    i=1

    while i < X_hat.shape[1]:
        t = X_hat[:,i].reshape((N,1)).T
        t_pad = np.pad(t, ((0,0),(i*np.int64(N/2),0)), mode='constant', constant_values=0)

        result_pad = np.pad(result_pad, ((0,0),(0,np.int64(N/2))), mode='constant', constant_values=0)
        result_pad += t_pad 
        i+=1
    print("Shape of recovered signal after inversing:",result_pad.shape)
    return result_pad

Function to calculate SNR value¶

In [36]:
def snr(r_sh_piano,re):
    numerator = r_sh_piano.T @ r_sh_piano
    denominator = (r_sh_piano - re).T @ (r_sh_piano - re)
    snr = 10 * np.log10(np.divide(numerator,denominator))
    return snr

Function to calculate M_bar masking¶

In [37]:
# Calculation of M_bar matrix
def m_bar(piano_res,ocean_res):
    num = np.absolute(piano_res)**2
    den = np.absolute(ocean_res)**2+np.absolute(piano_res)**2
    M_bar = np.divide(num,den)
    print("Shape of M_bar matrix:",M_bar.shape)
    return M_bar

Function to implement IBM¶

In [38]:
def ibm(piano_res,ocean_res):
    B = np.zeros((piano_res.shape))
    for row in range(piano_res.shape[0]):
        for col in range(piano_res.shape[1]):
            if np.absolute(piano_res[row,col]) > np.absolute(ocean_res[row,col]):
                B[row,col] = 1
        else:
            B[row,col] = 0

    print("Shape of the B matrix:",B.shape)
    return B

Both the recovered piano sounds from M_bar and IBM masking are very similar to the original piano sound. As SNR value increases, the better the quality of the sound. Hence, the signal with M_bar sounds slightly better than IBM¶

After using my own STFT and ISTFT implementation, though I was able to recover the signal properly, I didn't get the SNR value after M_bar and IBM masking in the range of 8 and 7. Hence, I used the library librosa to implement stft and istft again.¶
